# HotelAI Architecture

Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for full details. Follow these rules:

## Feature-First Layout

- `app/<route>/page.tsx` — thin Server Components: fetch data, wrap in `AppShell`, pass props
- `components/dashboard/<feature>/` — feature UI (Page, Table, Form, Dialogs, Stats, Filters)
- `lib/services/<domain>.service.ts` — read queries (no `"use server"`)
- `lib/services/<domain>.mutations.ts` — writes (`"use server"`, `revalidatePath`)
- `types/<domain>.ts` — shared entity types
- `components/ui/` — generic shadcn primitives only, no domain logic

## Naming

- Components: PascalCase (`BookingsTable.tsx`)
- Services: `<domain>.service.ts`, `<domain>.mutations.ts`
- Types: singular (`booking.ts`), exported as `type` not `enum`
- Routes: kebab-case folders, `page.tsx` inside

## Data Flow

1. Server page calls `getX()` from `*.service.ts`
2. Client feature component handles UI state (filters, dialogs)
3. Forms call Server Actions from `*.mutations.ts`
4. On success: `revalidatePath` + `router.refresh()` + `toast`

## Server Actions

- Input as typed object, throw on error, `revalidatePath("/route")` after mutation
- Business rules (availability, pricing) as private helpers in mutations file

## Multi-Tenancy

- All data scoped by `hotel_id` (currently hardcoded `hotel_aurora`)
- Never add queries without tenant filter

## Do Not

- Put Supabase calls in components (except legacy leads realtime)
- Put business logic in `app/` pages or `components/ui/`
- Create default exports for components (pages excepted)
